OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,390,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F389A1783696745
OL,3,CRetailers urged to suspend sales of
OL,4,Cdisposable BBQs during extreme heat
OL,6,FThe appeal follows increasing concerns
OL,7,Fabout the risk of fires being started
OL,8,Fby barbecues that are improperly used,
OL,9,Fdiscarded while still hot, or placed
OL,10,Fon flammable ground such as grass,
OL,11,Fheathland or woodland - especially
OL,12,Fduring the recent heatwave.
OL,14,FRetailers are being encouraged to
OL,15,Ffollow the British Retail Consortium's
OL,16,FVoluntary Guidelines for Disposable
OL,17,FBarbecues, which recommend that
OL,18,Fretailers suspend the sale of
OL,19,Fdisposable barbecues when weather
OL,20,Fconditions create a significant fire
OL,21,Frisk.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
